yet another silde description language & system

No more babysitting slides because of component dependencies.
The language is stupidly extensible, so you can finally stop living in cmd + c / cmd + v.
And with enough static checks, it catches stuff you missed in your slides before it gets a chance to embarrass you during the talk.

PDF rendering uses fpdf2 + pypdf and embeds Noto Sans JP / Noto Sans Mono /
Noto Emoji for full Japanese and emoji coverage. On first render the Zig backend invokes `third_party/fonts/fetch.py`, which downloads the variable Noto fonts from Google Fonts and instances per-weight
static TTFs into `third_party/fonts/`.

Setup:

  scripts/setup-md4c.sh
  zig build

This fetches the pinned MD4C revision into ignored `third_party/md4c/` sources
used by the Zig build.

VS Code extension:

1. Run `Developer: Install Extension from Location...`
2. Choose `editor/vscode/`
3. If `.ss` opens as Scheme, copy `editor/vscode/settings.sample.json` to
   `.vscode/settings.json`

Python runtime requirements:

  fpdf2 pypdf fonttools pillow

You can override the Python interpreter with the `SS_PYTHON` env var.


